.TH "SOVEREIGN-OSCTL-INSTALL" "1" "2026-07-14" "sovereign-os 0.3.0" "sovereign-os Operator Manual"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
sovereign-osctl-install - installation, profiles, customization, and
decommission
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl\f[R] \f[I]command\f[R] [\f[I]subcommand\f[R]]
[\f[I]options\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Bootstrap, profile selection, initialization, hooks, whitelabeling,
image installation, deployment paths, configuration snapshots, and
decommissioning.
.PP
This page owns 19 top-level commands.
Ownership is defined in
\f[V]docs/man/sovereign-osctl-command-topics.json\f[R] and checked
against the real dispatcher.
The synopsis and descriptions are grounded in the command handler or
delegated-script contract at this build revision.
The top-level help is a discovery summary, not an exhaustive grammar.
.SH SAFETY MODEL
.PP
Image writes and decommissioning are destructive.
Always run the plan form, verify the target fingerprint, keep the
running root out of scope, and supply the dedicated confirmation only
after reviewing the plan.
.PP
Read-only discovery should precede mutation.
JSON output, when offered, is the stable surface for automation; human
output is intended for direct operator use.
.SH COMMON WORKFLOW
.IP "1." 3
Confirm the installed revision with \f[B]sovereign-osctl version\f[R].
.IP "2." 3
Inspect the relevant \f[B]status\f[R], \f[B]show\f[R], \f[B]list\f[R],
\f[B]info\f[R], \f[B]plan\f[R], or \f[B]doctor\f[R] surface.
.IP "3." 3
Save machine-readable output when \f[V]--json\f[R] is available.
.IP "4." 3
Review profile, device, backend, policy, and target selection.
.IP "5." 3
Apply the smallest scoped mutation, then re-run health/status.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
sovereign-osctl profiles validate
sovereign-osctl init
sovereign-osctl install image --plan build/sain-01/output/sain-01.raw --to /dev/nvme1n1
sovereign-osctl decommission --plan
sovereign-osctl config-snapshot
\f[R]
.fi
.SH COMMAND REFERENCE
.SS profiles
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl profiles list\f[R]
List declared profiles
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl profiles show \f[R]
Print profile YAML (raw, no mixin resolution)
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl profiles show-effective  Print profile with mixins + parent resolved\f[R]
See the handler for behavior and options.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl profiles compare  \f[R]
Unified diff of two profiles\[cq] EFFECTIVE (resolved) state
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl profiles fork  \f[R]
Scaffold a new profile from with id (validates immediately)
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl profiles active\f[R]
Show active profile id
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl profiles switch \f[R]
Swap active profile (flags items requiring rebuild)
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl profiles validate\f[R]
Schema-validate all profiles (raw + resolved)
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl profiles generate-runtime   [\[en]out ]\f[R]
See the handler for behavior and options.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl profiles create-orchestration  [\[en]intent ] [\[en]conductor ]\f[R]
See the handler for behavior and options.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl profiles flex show [\[en]json]\f[R]
R224 (SDD-026 Z-3): print active profile +
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl profiles flex set   [\[en]json]\f[R]
See the handler for behavior and options.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl profiles flex reset [\[en]json] R224: clear every delta \[em] revert to YAML\f[R]
See the handler for behavior and options.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl profiles flex history [\[en]json]\f[R]
See the handler for behavior and options.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl profiles flex export [\[en]output PATH] [\[en]json]\f[R]
See the handler for behavior and options.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl profiles flex import  [\[en]mode replace|merge] [\[en]json]\f[R]
See the handler for behavior and options.
.SS whitelabel
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl whitelabel show\f[R]
Show active whitelabel branding
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl whitelabel apply \f[R]
Re-render whitelabel surfaces on the running system
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl whitelabel list\f[R]
List declared whitelabels
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl whitelabel diff \f[R]
Unified diff: active whitelabel →
.SS hooks
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl hooks list []\f[R]
List hooks declared in a profile (default: active)
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl hooks add   [\[en]id ] [\[en]mandatory] [\[en]profile ]\f[R]
See the handler for behavior and options.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl hooks remove  [\[en]profile ]\f[R]
See the handler for behavior and options.
.SS decommission
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl decommission {\[en]plan|plan}\f[R]
Preview all three destructive phases, targets, sizes, and commands.
Writes nothing and requires no destructive environment gate.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl decommission start\f[R]
Begin phase 1 interactively: confirm, then securely wipe the state
fabric at \f[V]tank/context\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl decommission pool\f[R]
Run phase 2 and destroy the configured ZFS pool.
Requires \f[V]SOVEREIGN_OS_CONFIRM_DESTROY=YES\f[R] and the hook\[cq]s
confirmation gates.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl decommission wipe\f[R]
Run phase 3 against block devices declared in
\f[V]SOVEREIGN_OS_WIPE_DEVICES\f[R].
Uses \f[V]blkdiscard\f[R] for SSDs or \f[V]shred\f[R] otherwise and
requires the destructive confirmation gate.
.SS install
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl install image  \[en]to \f[R]
Safely dd a built image to a target device
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl install image \[en]plan  \[en]to \f[R]
Show fingerprint + plan, do nothing
.SS bootstrap
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl bootstrap [arguments]\f[R]
Inspect and operate the master-spec bootstrap surface.
Use the command\[cq]s own help/status path before applying a bootstrap
action.
.SS init
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl init [\[en]non-interactive]\f[R]
Interactive setup wizard covering six decisions: profile, substrate,
Secure Boot, encryption, whitelabel, and agent layer
.SS wizard
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl wizard [arguments]\f[R]
Run the guided operator wizard surface.
It is distinct from \f[V]init\f[R], which writes the six-decision build
configuration.
